# Hub contributing (template skeleton only)

When **`session.json`** has `"mode": "hub"`, also follow [CONTRIBUTING.md](../../CONTRIBUTING.md):

- Keep examples generic (`my-app`, `my-agent`) — no real project or domain names
- Scope: session binding, repos registry, worktrees, hooks, docs, install — not domain features
- Edit product code in `sessions/<codename>/worktrees/<repo>/` — not hub root (`mode: hub` does not unlock root edits). Push PRs from the worktree feature branch.
- Before opening a hub PR, run:

```bash
python3 scripts/test_session_binding.py
python3 scripts/test_git_remotes.py
python3 scripts/test_hub_upgrade.py
python3 scripts/test_workflow_plan_loop.py
python3 scripts/test_workflow_gates.py
python3 scripts/test_workflow_code_review.py
python3 scripts/test_workflow_resume.py
python3 scripts/test_workflow_plan_reviewer_rules.py
python3 scripts/test_hub_git.py
python3 scripts/test_workflow_delivery.py
python3 scripts/test_workflow_pr_creation.py
python3 scripts/test_workflow_ci_observe.py
python3 scripts/test_workflow_inbox_gate.py
```

- Open from a feature branch; wait for CI (`test` workflow)
- **Do not** use `gh pr merge --auto` or merge unless the maintainer explicitly asks
